      "content": "but i dont have any antibiotic ointment here and i really dont want to spend the money or time at a clinic. i have some manuka honey in the pantry and i read online that it's actually better for skin than that chemical stuff. if i just clean it with some water and then put a thick layer of the honey on it, won't that keep the bacteria away and help it close up? it seems a lot easier than driving all the way to the ER for a little cut.",
